---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
			description="A bit about Aadit Suryawanshi — building language models from first principles and learning by shipping systems."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<main>
			<section class="about-hero">
				<div class="container">
					<p class="kicker">About me</p>
					<h2>Aadit Suryawanshi</h2>
					<p class="lede">
						I like understanding systems beneath the abstractions. Rather than treating models and
						frameworks as black boxes, I enjoy implementing them from first principles to understand
						how they work and where their trade-offs lie.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section>
				<div class="container prose">
					<p>
						My interests span the full AI stack—from training and evaluating language models to
						building distributed backend systems, retrieval pipelines, and full-stack AI applications.
						I'm particularly interested in turning research ideas into reliable, scalable products.
					</p>
					<p>
						I learn by building. Most of my projects begin with a question I'm curious about and grow
						into end-to-end systems that combine machine learning, software engineering, and practical
						experimentation.
					</p>
			
					<h3>What I've Been Up To</h3>
					<p>I've always been curious about how things work. As a kid, 
						I spent way too much time building random projects, taking things apart, 
						and dreaming about becoming a scientist one day.
					</p>
					<p>When I was 18, my interests took a sharp turn. For reasons that mostly involved watching one too many military movies, 
						I decided I wanted to join the Indian Army. I cleared the written examination three times, 
						but the selection process doesn't end there. Candidates also go through a five-day assessment called the SSB interview that 
						tests leadership, decision-making, communication, teamwork, and psychological aptitude. 
						I made it to that stage every time but was eventually conferenced out.
					</p>
					<p>That chapter ended, so naturally I thought, "What's the next best thing?" The obvious answer, 
						apparently, was becoming an MMA fighter.
					</p>
					<p>I trained for about a year, competed in Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu, and even won a tournament in the 67 kg division. More importantly, I learned discipline, consistency, 
						and that getting choked repeatedly is a surprisingly effective teacher.
					</p>
					<p>Eventually I realized that while I loved training, I didn't want to dedicate my life to fighting.</p>
					<p>Around that time I found my way back to programming. At first I was just building things and trying different areas of software, 
						but over time I became fascinated by machine learning and AI. Reading research papers, implementing ideas from scratch, 
						and running my own experiments reminded me of the kid who wanted to be a scientist—not because of the title, 
						but because discovering how things work is genuinely fun.
					</p>
					<p>These days I'm happiest when I'm building AI systems, training models, or spending hours understanding a paper well enough to implement it myself. 
						There's still a lot I don't know, which is probably my favorite part.
						 I plan to keep learning, keep experimenting, and hopefully contribute something meaningful along the way.
					</p>
					<p>Anyway, thanks for reading.</p>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Header />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.about-hero {
		background: var(--paper-deep);
	}
	.lede {
		max-width: none;
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}
	.about-body .prose p {
		max-width: none;
	}
</style>
